  "summary": "Fixed Vampire invisible Shield Bug (all language)",
  "descriptionHtml": "Also available at [url=http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=87439591]Steam Workshop[/url]\r<br />This Fix is part of the [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/19/]Unofficial Skyrim Patch[/url] and obsolete if you have installed the USKP.\r<br />\r<br />This mod should work with any language.\r<br />The Mod is compatible with any version of Skyrim, inclusive Dawnguard.\r<br />\r<br />Please endorse this mod if you like it.\r<br />\r<br />[b][color=green]Short problem introduction:[/color][/b]\r<br />\r<br />If your Character turns into an Vampire there are a few Shield&#39;s and other items that aren&#39;t set to the Vampire-Race, so they are getting invisible.\r<br />This Fix should make them visible again.\r<br />\r<br />[b][color=green]What it does:[/color][/b]\r<br />\r<br />Following items are now visible if your Character turns into an Vampire:\r<br />- Blades Shield\r<br />- Ebony Shield\r<br />- Thieve Guild Hoods\r<br />- Thieve Guild Leader Hood\r<br />- Amulet of Zenithar\r<br />- Penitus Oculatus Helmet\r<br />\r<br />[b][color=yellow]Bugs:[/color][/b]\r<br />None so far, please report if you find some.\r<br />\r<br />[color=yellow][b]Install:[/b][/color]\r<br />Copy the &#34;data&#34; folder from the archive to your Skyrim directory.\r<br />If asked to overwrite, say yes.\r<br />Start the Skyrim launcher, go to &#34;Data Files&#34; and make sure the files are activated.\r<br />\r<br />[color=yellow][b]Uninstall:[/b][/color]\r<br />Delete the invisible_shield_fix.esp from your &#34;...&#92;Skyrim&#92;data&#34; directory.",
